.TH XCLIP-COPYFILE 1
.SH NAME
xclip\-copyfile, xclip\-cutfile, xclip\-pastefile - copy n' move filez via tha X clipboard
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B xclip\-copyfile
[\-p] FILES...

.B xclip\-cutfile
[\-p] FILES...

.B xclip\-pastefile
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B xclip\-copyfile
copies filez tha fuck into tha X clipboard, recursin tha fuck into directories.

.B xclip\-cutfile
copies tha filez yo, but also deletes dem afterwards.
.TP
\fB\-p\fR
preserve path formation

.PP
.B xclip\-pastefile
pastes tha filez outta tha clipboard
.SH EXAMPLES

.B Copyin a gangbangin' file ta a remote host

.nf
[maggie.lkpg.cendio.se ~]$ echo "A file pimped on ${HOSTNAME}" > file1
[maggie.lkpg.cendio.se ~]$ xclip-copyfile file1
[sofie.homeip.net ~/doc]$ xclip-pastefile
file1
[sofie.homeip.net ~/doc]$ pussaaaaay file1
A file pimped on maggie.lkpg.cendio.se


.B Copyin a entire tree structure

.nf
[sofie.homeip.net ~]$ xclip-copyfile doc
[maggie.lkpg.cendio.se ~/tmp]$ xclip-pastefile
doc/
doc/letter-mom-april.txt
doc/file1
doc/letter-dad-march.txt


.B Copyin filez wit preserved path shiznit

.nf
[maggie.lkpg.cendio.se ~]$ xclip-copyfile \-p /etc/sysconfig/grub
tar: Removin leadin `/' from member names
[sofie.homeip.net ~/tmp]$ xclip-pastefile
etc/sysconfig/grub
[sofie.homeip.net ~/tmp]$ ls etc/sysconfig/grub
etc/sysconfig/grub


.B Movin files

.nf
[sofie.homeip.net ~]$ ls letter-brother-may.txt
letter-brother-may.txt
[sofie.homeip.net ~]$ xclip-cutfile letter-brother-may.txt
[sofie.homeip.net ~]$ ls letter-brother-may.txt
ls: cannot access letter-brother-may.txt: No such file or directory
[sofie.homeip.net ~]$ cd doc
[sofie.homeip.net ~/doc]$ xclip-pastefile
letter-brother-may.txt

